Rules-Game Settings: Default timer: 60s

Info-Software Needed: It might be easier if commentators have the X|S version of Samsho
Rules-Notes:
AMAKUSA-SPECIFIC: Due to increased desync bugs associated with this character, you MUST set your delay frames to 3 if someone plays this character.

DESYNCS: Samurai Shodown rollback is subject to many desync-related bugs. In the event of a room crash, the default policy is to replay the game regardless of rounds and rage meter.

Games commonly desync for one player at the end of matches. The losing player's game will freeze, but the winning player will "play it out" as if they won. If this happens, the "losing" player should show a screenshot of the freeze to a TO so that we know to have the match replayed.

Players are entitled to either of the following:
1) A lag test game before their set starts
2) A host-swap request to help mitigate netcode problems
Please let a TO know if you'd like either of these.

STAGES: Due to the presence/absence of foreground objects that may contribute to rollback issues, please follow these guidelines for stages:
Recommended: Nikko, Kabuki Estate, Dojo, Greenhell
Recommended against: Mikatagahara Field, Sumida River, Galleon

Players have the right to insist on a recommended stage.

DELAY FRAME GUIDELINES: Try to use 1 delay frame for every 50ms of ping. E.g. 1 frame for 57ms, 2 frames for 104ms, etc.
$-Prizes: Prizes from SNK potentially if we can reach out to them

Rules-Notes:
In-game settings: Set Time 90, Set Points 15, Winning Sets 2.

Random Start: First stage per match is set to Random. Hit the random button twice, then hit select to lock in the stage.

Banned stage: Casino. If selected on accident, exit the match and select another stage. 

Winner is character locked, loser may counter-pick both stage and character.

Matches are 2/3 (Excepting Winners Grand Finals, 3/5).

If Sudden Death occurs and no players score, return to the same stage, with the same characters. First player to score wins.

Dave's Stupid Rule: a Player may not choose a stage on which they have previously won within the current match.
